{
  "text": "The present data suggested that multiple measurements of salivary cortisol levels may be useful for optimization of metyrapone treatment by visualization of diurnal cortisol levels. Although multiple collections are required, salivary collection is a less of a burden for patients. Furthermore, salivary samples are stable and can be easily stored [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Therefore, it is feasible in outpatient clinics.",
